  "text": "The admin API implementation in envoy is organized under source/server/admin/. The central file is admin.cc which contains AdminImpl \u2014 this implements addHandler() for registering admin endpoints, createFilterChain() for setting up the admin filter chain (using the inner class AdminFilterChain defined in admin.h), and the routing that wires all handler registrations. admin_filter.cc implements AdminFilter which is the HTTP filter that processes admin requests. Each endpoint has a dedicated handler file: clusters_handler.cc (/clusters), listeners_handler.cc (/listeners), config_dump_handler.cc (/config_dump), and stats_handler.cc (/stats). The stats endpoint also relies on stats_request.cc (chunked stats streaming) and prometheus_stats.cc (Prometheus format rendering for /stats/prometheus).",
